# Overview
- Qground control ground station is a very simple and easy ground station to use as a beginer due to the simplicity in the calibration process of various sensors also it calibrate the ESCs easily by going to power setting and clicking on Calibrate the ESC
- Qground control can be installed on android and iOS devices 
- you may need to define a key for the telemetry if it didn't connect auto by going to ....
- there is some paramaters you will need to know about them about safety, signal value and battery failsafe
- In tuning it is very easy just enter the valuse and click save and you will see from graphs the response of the quadcopter if affected by external action
- Qground is easy in mission setup just enter the waypoints and define the speed and height of the quadcopter at each waypoint the first waypoint is taking off the ground when you are in Auto mode
## Warrning:
- study carly the changes of modes while flying because each made has a default setting which may be different from the current status
## Note:
- even the battery is full Qground may read lower battery level also when using a power supply it reads 75% 

# steps of use:
1- Download the software of Qground and complete installation 
2- after openning the reciever and powering the pixhawk the telemetry will fix and parameters will be read 
3- start adding the configuration and complete the wizard until calibration ends
